$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Ninu mathimatiki ati imọ-ẹrọ kọnputa, hexadecimal (tun ipilẹ 16, tabi hex) jẹ eto nọmba ipo ipo pẹlu radix, tabi ipilẹ, ti 16. O nlo awọn ami iyasọtọ mẹrindilogun, pupọ julọ awọn aami 0-9 lati ṣe aṣoju awọn iye odo si mẹsan, ati A, B, C, D, E, F (tabi omiiran a–f) lati ṣe aṣoju awọn iye mẹwa si meedogun. Fun apẹẹrẹ, nọmba hexadecimal 2AF3 jẹ dọgba, ni eleemewa, si (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , tabi 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Nọmba hexadecimal kọọkan jẹ aṣoju awọn nọmba alakomeji mẹrin (awọn die-die) (ti a tun pe ni “nibble”), ati lilo akọkọ ti akọsilẹ hexadecimal jẹ bi aṣoju ore-eniyan ti awọn iye koodu koodu alakomeji ni iṣiro ati ẹrọ itanna oni-nọmba. Fun apẹẹrẹ, awọn iye baiti le wa lati 0 si 255 (eleemewa) ṣugbọn o le jẹ aṣoju ni irọrun diẹ sii bi awọn nọmba hexadecimal meji ni iwọn 00 si FF. Hexadecimal tun jẹ lilo nigbagbogbo lati ṣe aṣoju awọn adirẹsi iranti kọnputa.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex jẹ abbreviation ti Hexadecimal, eyiti o da lori ipilẹ -16 ẹya ati pe o lo fun irọrun bi awọn ilana si awọn kọnputa ṣe jẹ aṣoju. Eto nọmba awọn aami 16 yii ni idagbasoke bi ọna lati dena nọmba alakomeji 8-bit kan, nitorinaa data le ṣe koodu sinu awọn kọnputa laisi wahala. O le ṣe titẹ ati tẹ ni lilo awọn nọmba hex oriṣiriṣi meji pẹlu nọmba hex kọọkan ti n ṣe afihan nibble tabi boya ọna kika 4-bits kan.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Eto nọmba yii nlo awọn aami 16 ti o jẹ aṣoju ni ibiti o wa lati 0-9 tabi AF. 0–9 jẹ aṣoju awọn nọmba to mẹsan nigba ti AF jẹ aṣoju nipasẹ nomba 10–15. Bi akawe si awọn oriṣi mẹta ti awọn ọna ṣiṣe nọmba, eto nọmba hexadecimal ni a gba pe o jẹ ọkan ti o munadoko julọ.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Koodu hexadecimal rẹ ko wulo';
